  "text": "For group level analyses we created a group DARTEL template [CITATION_1] using the whole brain structural scans from each participant's first visit. Functional images were warped via the group space to MNI space, then spatially smoothed using a Gaussian smoothing kernel of 4 Â 4 Â 4 mm full-width at half maximum, which we found to be the minimum to satisfy the smoothness assumptions of random field theory-based multiple comparisons correction in SPM. GLMs were created as above (with one modification e the fixation baseline condition was left unmodelled). After estimating the GLMs we summarised results at the group level using one sample t-tests in SPM. Where conjunctions are reported, these are tests against the conjunction null, that is to say a logical AND across conditions. Results are reported using topological FDR correction at p < .05 with cluster forming threshold of p < .01 unless stated otherwise.",
